Constructor

detaileddescription.para: This is the constructor, setting variables to default values

briefdescription.para: Destructor

detaileddescription.para: This is the destructor, nothing to report here

briefdescription.para: This method initializes all of the dynamics and variables for the s/c

detaileddescription.para: This method is used to initialize the simulation by registering all of the states, linking the dynamicEffectors, stateEffectors, and the hub, initialize gravity, and initialize the sim with the initial conditions specified in python for the simulation

briefdescription.para: This method computes the total energy and momentum of the s/c

detaileddescription.para: This method is used to find the total energy and momentum of the spacecraft. It finds the total orbital energy, total orbital angular momentum, total rotational energy and total rotational angular momentum. These values are used for validation purposes.

briefdescription.para: This method computes the total mass properties of the s/c

detaileddescription.para: This method is used to update the mass properties of the entire spacecraft using contributions from stateEffectors

briefdescription.para: This method computes the force and torque from the stateEffectors

detaileddescription.para: This method is used to find the force and torque that each stateEffector is applying to the spacecraft. These values are held in the stateEffector class. Additionally, the stateDerivative value is behind the state values because they are calculated in the intergrator calls

This method is used to reset the module.

briefdescription.para: Method to write all of the class output messages

detaileddescription.para: This is the method where the messages of the state of vehicle are written

briefdescription.para: Runtime hook back into Basilisk arch

detaileddescription.para: This method is a part of sysModel and is used to integrate the state and update the state in the messaging system

briefdescription.para: Method to get access to the hub's states.

detaileddescription.para: This method allows the spacecraft to have access to the current state of the hub for MRP switching, writing messages, and calculating energy and momentum

briefdescription.para: This method computes the equations of motion for the whole system

detaileddescription.para: This method is solving Xdot = F(X,t) for the system. The hub needs to calculate its derivatives, along with all of the stateEffectors. The hub also has gravity and dynamicEffectors acting on it and these relationships are controlled in this method. At the end of this method all of the states will have their corresponding state derivatives set in the dynParam Manager thus solving for Xdot
